{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YNnVdJuhF2Z2EqM8fVPBPJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package spring.tutorial.roster;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     5→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     6→import org.springframework.boot.test.context.SpringBootTest;\n     7→import org.springframework.test.annotation.DirtiesContext;\n     8→import spring.tutorial.roster.request.Request;\n     9→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n    10→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.PlayerDetails;\n    11→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n    12→\n    13→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;\n    14→\n    15→@SpringBootTest\n    16→@DirtiesContext(classMode = DirtiesContext.ClassMode.AFTER_EACH_TEST_METHOD)\n    17→class RequestQueriesIT {\n    18→\n    19→  @Autowired\n    20→  Request request;\n    21→\n    22→  @Test\n    23→  void queryScenarios() {\n    24→    request.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"Lq\",\"Summer\",\"soccer\"));\n    25→    request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"Tq\",\"Tigers\",\"Austin\"), \"Lq\");\n    26→    request.createPlayer(\"Pa\",\"Alice\",\"Forward\",100);\n    27→    request.createPlayer(\"Pb\",\"Bob\",\"Goalie\",120);\n    28→    request.createPlayer(\"Pz\",\"Zed\",\"Forward\",90);\n    29→    request.addPlayer(\"Pa\",\"Tq\");\n    30→    request.addPlayer(\"Pb\",\"Tq\");\n    31→\n    32→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersByPosition(\"Forward\")).containsAll(List.of(\"Pa\",\"Pz\")));\n    33→    assertEquals(List.of(\"Pb\"), ids(request.getPlayersByHigherSalary(\"Alice\")));\n    34→    assertEquals(List.of(\"Pa\"), ids(request.getPlayersBySalaryRange(95,110)));\n    35→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersByLeagueId(\"Lq\")).containsAll(List.of(\"Pa\",\"Pb\")));\n    36→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersBySport(\"soccer\")).containsAll(List.of(\"Pa\",\"Pb\")));\n    37→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersByCity(\"Austin\")).containsAll(List.of(\"Pa\",\"Pb\")));\n    38→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersNotOnTeam()).contains(\"Pz\"));\n    39→    assertEquals(List.of(\"Pa\"), ids(request.getPlayersByPositionAndName(\"Forward\",\"Alice\")));\n    40→    assertEquals(List.of(\"Lq\"), request.getLeaguesOfPlayer(\"Pa\").stream().map(LeagueDetails::getId).toList());\n    41→    assertTrue(request.getSportsOfPlayer(\"Pa\").contains(\"soccer\"));\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  private static List<String> ids(List<PlayerDetails> list) {\n    45→    return list.stream().map(PlayerDetails::getId).toList();\n    46→  }\n    47→}\n    48→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3b591f7e-183a-4681-abab-4c3b92831289","uuid":"381a9c29-fc73-47aa-ac25-92858da86fe0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0144G6DyxC4Awba41K9WxW6y","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package spring.tutorial.roster;\n     2→\n     3→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     4→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     5→import org.springframework.boot.test.context.SpringBootTest;\n     6→import spring.tutorial.roster.request.Request;\n     7→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n     8→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n     9→\n    10→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\n    11→\n    12→@SpringBootTest\n    13→class RequestSmokeTest {\n    14→\n    15→  @Autowired\n    16→  Request request;\n    17→\n    18→  @Test\n    19→  void roundTrip() {\n    20→    request.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"L1\",\"Summer Fun\",\"soccer\"));\n    21→    request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"T1\",\"Tigers\",\"Austin\"), \"L1\");\n    22→    request.createPlayer(\"P1\",\"Alice\",\"Forward\",100000);\n    23→    request.addPlayer(\"P1\",\"T1\");\n    24→    assertEquals(1, request.getPlayersOfTeam(\"T1\").size());\n    25→  }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3b591f7e-183a-4681-abab-4c3b92831289","uuid":"ddcad518-2544-4d15-b8f4-2f305c6d20ec"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JMPxMrC3MDMesVv8a3bEMK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# VCS\n     2→.git/\n     3→\n     4→# Maven\n     5→.mvn/\n     6→**/.mvn/\n     7→mvnw\n     8→mvnw.cmd\n     9→**/mvnw\n    10→**/mvnw.cmd\n    11→target/\n    12→**/target/\n    13→pom.xml.tag\n    14→pom.xml.releaseBackup\n    15→pom.xml.versionsBackup\n    16→pom.xml.next\n    17→release.properties\n    18→dependency-reduced-pom.xml\n    19→buildNumber.properties\n    20→\n    21→# IDE / Editor\n    22→.vscode/\n    23→**/.vscode/\n    24→.zed/\n    25→**/.zed/\n    26→.idea/\n    27→**/.idea/\n    28→*.iml\n    29→*.ipr\n    30→*.iws\n    31→\n    32→# OS\n    33→.DS_Store\n    34→**/.DS_Store\n    35→Thumbs.db\n    36→ehthumbs.db\n    37→\n    38→# Logs / temp\n    39→*.log\n    40→*.tmp\n    41→*.temp\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3b591f7e-183a-4681-abab-4c3b92831289","uuid":"cc63f486-130c-474f-94a7-8f70d17ea933"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01C1b1AzJWMZYJYz2Aez6npf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me analyze the migration requirements:\n\n**Current state:** Spring Boot 3.1 application with JPA, REST controllers, H2 database\n**Target:** Jakarta EE (standalone, no Spring Boot)\n\nThe migration involves:\n1. Replacing Spring Boot with a Jakarta EE runtime (e.g., Open Liberty, Payara, or WildFly) \n2. Replacing Spring Data JPA repositories with Jakarta Persistence EntityManager\n3. Replacing Spring REST annotations with Jakarta REST (JAX-RS) annotations\n4. Replacing Spring DI with Jakarta CDI\n5. Updating configuration and Dockerfile\n\nI'll use Open Liberty as the Jakarta EE runtime since it's lightweight and well-suited for this.\n\nLet me note the file with a comma in the name - `RequestSmokeText,java` - this is actually a test file that should be `RequestSmokeTest.java`."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2299,"cache_read_input_tokens":42156,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2299,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":692},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3b591f7e-183a-4681-abab-4c3b92831289","uuid":"81fe0dd6-5021-45fc-ae37-713ded6a442c"}
